 <figcaption id="img-caption"> 
      Heart-Shaped Face Barn Owl
    </figcaption>
    
  <div id="tribute-info">
  Barn owls (Tytoninae) are one of the two families of

owls, the other being the true owls. They are medium to large

sized with large heart-shaped faces and long legs. They live in

a wide range of habitats from temperate latitudes to the tropics.

They are mostly nocturnal, and generally non-migratory.
